Brazil will take on Nigeria in an international friendly match this Sunday in Singapore. Gernot Rohr is preparing his team for November’s 2021 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers with Benin Republic and Lesotho. The Super Eagles lost 3-0 to the Selecao in their last meeting at the National Stadium in Abuja. Brazil come into this encounter, after drawing 1-1 with Senegal on Thursday in another friendly. Kick off is 1pm West African time. Brazil XI vs Nigeria: Ederson; Alves, Thiago Silva, Marquinhos, Lodi; Arthur, Casemiro; Firmino, Jesus, Everton, Neymar. Nigeria XI vs Brazil: Uzoho, Awaziem, Troost-Ekong, Ajayi, Collins, Iwobi, Osimhen, Moses Simon, Aribo, Ndidi, Chukwueze. Sunday, October 13
First half: Joe Aribo gives Nigeria a 1-0 lead. Half time. Second half: Casemiro makes it 1-1. Full time: It ends 1-1 between Nigeria and Brazil. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.